<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>OTP Verification</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 20px;
        background-color: #f4f4f4;
        color: #333;
      }
      .container {
        max-width: 600px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        background-color: #ffffff;
        padding: 20px;
        border-radius: 5px;
        box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
      }
      h2 {
        color: #2c3e50;
      }
      .otp-code {
        font-size: 24px;
        font-weight: bold;
        color: #e74c3c;
        margin: 20px 0;
      }
      .footer {
        font-size: 12px;
        color: #7f8c8d;
        margin-top: 20px;
        text-align: center;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Hi there!</h2>
      <p>
        We received a request to verify your account with Code Sphere. Your
        One-Time Password (OTP) is provided below.
      </p>
      <p class="otp-code">OTP: <%= otp %></p>
      <p>
        This OTP is valid for <%= validity %>. Please do not share it with
        anyone.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you didnâ€™t request this, please ignore this email or contact support
        at <a href="mailto:support@codesphere.com">support@codesphere.com</a>.
      </p>
      <div class="footer">
        <p>&copy; 2025 Code Sphere. All rights reserved.</p>
        <p>
          This email was sent to you because you (or someone else) signed up for
          or requested an action on our platform.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
